org.greatage.ioc
Class ServiceAdditionalResources<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.greatage.ioc.ServiceAdditionalResources<T>
Type Parameters:
T - service type
All Implemented Interfaces:
ServiceResources<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ServiceBuildResources, ServiceConfigureResources, ServiceDecorateResources
public abstract class ServiceAdditionalResources<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ServiceResources<T>

This class represents ServiceResources proxy implementation that is used for extending its default functionality by adding additional resources. Its implementations are used for different service build phases.

Since:
1.0
Author:
Ivan Khalopik

getResource

public <E> E getResource(java.lang.Class<E> resourceClass,
                         java.lang.annotation.Annotation... annotations)
Gets resource to service by its type and annotations used. It can provide logger for service, injected symbols configured by SymbolSource (needs Symbol annotation), injected services by id (needs Inject annotation) or services by their interfaces by default. Firstly tries to retrieve resource from additional resources.

getResource in interface ServiceResources<T>
